title: No. 3 Golden Bears Power Past No. 1 'Dogs
text:
No. 3 Golden Bears Power Past No. 1 'Dogs 
By Zach Schneider October 6, 2015 Updated Oct 6, 2015 at 9:50 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The No. 3 Concordia-St. Paul volleyball team played a crisp match on Tuesday night en route to a 3-1 win over the No. 1 University of Minnesota Duluth, handing the Bulldogs their third loss of 2015. 
Anna Schlaak led the Golden Bears with 16 kills in the winning effort, leading an offense that hit for a .318 hitting percentage. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Mariah Scharf was the Bulldogs' leader with 17 kills in the match, with Taylor Wissbroecker adding 12 and Sarah Kelly finishing with 11. 
UMD, however, only hit .84 as a team and finished with 30 attack errors compared with only 14 for Concordia-St. Paul. 
UMD is now (13-3) overall this season and (6-2) in the Northern Sun Intercollegiate Conference (NSIC).
